04/25/2020 - RIDOC Transparency report:

As of today, there are a total of seven RIDOC staff who have tested positive for COVID19, and the count for sentenced housed inmates continue to be zero.

New Commitments: ...
A new commitment was brought tonight to the Intake Service Center (ISC) by the State Police who had tested positive for Covid-19 out in the community. As it is the protocol in these cases, the new commitment was placed in full Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) and was received by ISC officers also wearing full PPE.
Just like with the previous commitments, the inmate was placed in a negative-pressure room and remains in medical isolation for everyone’s safety. Our staff is fully prepared for such scenarios and we are taking every precaution to make sure everyone is safe. This makes a total of two new commitments in our custody held in medical isolation due to the virus. Again, the number of positive cases within the sentenced, general population inmates is still zero.

Thank you and please be safe out there.
